    h3 usage
    p just use the tag <strong>mn-dialog</strong> and <strong>mn-option</strong>, e.g.
    mn-code.html.
      <mn-dialog>
        <option value="#fff">White</option>
        <option value="#000">Black</option>
      </mn-dialog>

    p To begin with an value, you can use the attribute <strong>selected</strong> in tag option
    mn-code.html.
      <mn-dialog>
        <option value="#fff">White</option>
        <option value="#000" selected>Black</option>
      </mn-dialog>

    p Or just use the attribute <strong>value</strong> in mn-dialog
    mn-code.html.
      <mn-dialog value="#fff">
        <option value="#fff">White</option>
        <option value="#000">Black</option>
      </mn-dialog>

    p If you want set the value from javascript, just assign a value to property <strong>value</strong>, e.g.
    mn-code.js.
      document.querySelector('mn-dialog').value = '#000'
  
